!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

tremendous /trɪˈmɛndəs/

1. ADJ You use tremendous to emphasize how strong a feeling or quality is, or how large an amount is. 非常的; 巨大的 [强调] 

例： I felt a tremendous pressure on my chest. 我感到胸口有股巨大的压力。 

2. tremendously ADV 非常地; 极大地 

例： I thought they played tremendously well, didn't you? 我认为他们表演得非常好，你不觉得吗？ 

3. ADJ You can describe someone or something as tremendous when you think they are very good or very impressive. 极好的; 精彩的 

例： I thought it was absolutely tremendous. 我觉得它绝对精彩。

</div>

